{"id":"open-place","term":"Open place","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p><a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:14\">Gen. 38:14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:21\">21</a>, mar. Enaim; the same probably as Enam (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 15:34\">Josh. 15:34</a>), a city in the lowland or Shephelah.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 38:14","Genesis 38:21","Joshua 15:34"]}